For context: random chance on 10-class classification is 10\%. These
scores are 2.7--4.7x chance. State-of-the-art continual learning methods
achieve 90\%+ on these benchmarks. MorphoBASE is not competing on this
axis.

What matters here is:

\begin{enumerate}
\def\labelenumi{\arabic{enumi}.}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  All four benchmarks are \textbf{seed-stable} across 5 seeds
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  All four are \textbf{mechanism-supported}: ablating growth, stress, or
  Z-field produces measurable performance changes, confirming that task
  competence depends on organismal mechanisms
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  Permuted-FashionMNIST shows \textbf{very low forgetting} (0.005) and
  \textbf{positive backward transfer} (BWT = +0.025), meaning earlier
  tasks actually improve slightly after later learning --- a signature
  of genuine knowledge consolidation rather than interference
  \end{quote}
\end{enumerate}

\hypertarget{non-visual-control-and-symbolic-tasks-stack-d}{%
\paragraph{Non-visual control and symbolic tasks (Stack
D)}\label{non-visual-control-and-symbolic-tasks-stack-d}}

\begin{longtable}[]{@{}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 10\tabcolsep) * \real{0.2059}}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 10\tabcolsep) * \real{0.1946}}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 10\tabcolsep) * \real{0.0803}}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 10\tabcolsep) * \real{0.1219}}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 10\tabcolsep) * \real{0.1385}}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 10\tabcolsep) * \real{0.2586}}@{}}
\toprule()
\begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
Benchmark
\end{minipage} & \begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
Mean Score
\end{minipage} & \begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
