These non-visual tasks are substantially stronger. Gridworld Remap is
the cleanest result in the entire project: perfectly stable across seeds
with zero forgetting. Sequential Rules shows low forgetting (0.021) with
a tight standard deviation.

These results demonstrate that the organism is a general substrate, not
a visual-task-specific architecture.

\hypertarget{lesion-aware-task-bridges}{%
\paragraph{Lesion-aware task bridges}\label{lesion-aware-task-bridges}}

Under lesion conditions, the organism retains task competence while
ablation baselines degrade:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  \textbf{Lesion Sequential Rules}: organism retains 58.33\% accuracy;
  no-growth drops to 50.00\%, no-Z-field drops to 46.67\%
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  \textbf{Lesion Gridworld Remap}: organism retains function; ablation
  shows Z-field dependency
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  \textbf{Lesion Split-MNIST}: organism retains function under damage
  \end{quote}
\end{itemize}

\hypertarget{organism-vs.-baseline-comparison}{%
\subsubsection{4.8 Organism vs. baseline
comparison}\label{organism-vs.-baseline-comparison}}

\includegraphics[width=6.925in,height=2.83889in]{vertopal_6e525fe6863342d18c048d95760e16e4/media/image7.png}\emph{\textbf{Figure
7: Lesion-Aware Competence vs. Baselines.} A comparison of task
retention after injury. MorphoBASE explicitly prioritizes repair and
retained competence over raw, undamaged benchmark scores, outperforming
static MLP and Transformer baselines when evaluated under damage-aware
conditions.}

The organism is strongest when the task rewards repair, remap, and
persistence. It is not trying to beat transformers or MLPs on raw
undamaged benchmark score.

\hypertarget{frontier-mechanisms-exploratory}{%
\subsection{5. Frontier mechanisms
(exploratory)}\label{frontier-mechanisms-exploratory}}

\includegraphics[width=6.925in,height=2.76458in]{vertopal_6e525fe6863342d18c048d95760e16e4/media/image8.png}\emph{\textbf{Figure
8: Communication Architecture and Frontier Probes.} Evidence supporting
the organism\textquotesingle s multi-channel communication framework.
The left panel displays the spatial localization ratios of five
exploratory channels, ensuring bounded behavior. The right panel
demonstrates a causal "light cone" of perturbation, which changes
interpretably when specific channels (Z-Memory, Conductance, Stress
Sharing) are ablated.}

Five additional communication channels are implemented but designated as
non-gating exploratory probes:

\begin{longtable}[]{@{}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 2\tabcolsep) * \real{0.5270}}
